elwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=baracasplaguebearer>Baracas Plaguebearer</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 9<br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/11/02 1:47:25 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2616.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_sword.gif" align=absmiddle>  Sit Agro</span><hr size=1> Im sure this has been brought up in the past, but I havent seen anything recently.<br>
<br>
I made a macro<br>
<br>
/sit on<br>
/taunt<br>
/sit off<br>
/attack on<br>
<br>
<br>
It *tears* agro off whomever I want when I use it.  I tried it shortly in poi today and had no problems whatsoever getting agro.  I found its only use when something has agro on something else. If I used it in the middle of battle or when there was only very little agro established on someone else, it would smash me pretty good.  However, it seemed the time it took to go from /taunt to /sit off was the time it took for the heavily agroed mob to turn around, therefore avoiding the heavy sit damage. By the time it hit me after the /sit off went off the damage I took was avoided or mitigated.<br>
<br>
<br>
My logic lead me here. When you sit you create a kind of temporary agro. But when you you hit taunt when you sit wouldnt that set you at that higher agro rating? Therefore making a more powerful and dangerous taunt?<br>
<br>
<br>
I encountered two major problems with this, one of which seems unavoidable.  <br>
<br>
Problem 1<br>
<br>
If the person Im trying to get agro off of doesnt have sufficient agro, when I sit the mob will turn on me and I take a full quad of damage.  <br>
<br>
Timing and judgement seems would fix this one.<br>
<br>
<br>
Problem 2<br>
<br>
People flip out when they see you sit in the middle of battle.<br>
<br>
<br>
This seems like such a powerful way of getting agro it must be too good to be true.  Am I right in my short test or just lucky?<br>
<br>
 <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://216.119.111.158/eddieland.gif"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=wyrdlan>Wyrdlan</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_lightning.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 91<br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/11/02 1:58:52 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2616.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.eq-viatores.org/book.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_sword.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Sit Agro</span><hr size=1> My kneejerk reaction would be no.<br>
I'd think it would be like taunting when you already have agro, to taunt while sitting.  I'm not sure taunt would do ANYTHING in that case. If your taunt works and the mob agros because taunted, he would have agroed on the taunt anyway, at least until someone else does something. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://pub38.ezboard.com/feqtraderscornerfrm38.showMessage?topicID=409.topic"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.eq-viatores.org/sig.php"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=turomtoesmasher>Turom Toesmasher</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>will kick your @$$</span><br>  Posts: 442<br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/11/02 2:08:42 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2616.topic&index=2>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.gaiahealing.com/everquest/turom_head.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_sword.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Sit Agro</span><hr size=1> 1) Taunt, if successful, will put you just barely at the top of the hate list.<br>
<br>
2) Sitting only pulls temporary agro.  As soon as you stand, the mob will *instantly* turn back to whomever is at the top of their hate list.<br>
<br>
So if your taunt was successful, then you didn't need to sit.  If your taunt was not successful, then the mob is simply going to turn back to whomever is on the top of the hate list.  <br>
<br>
One of three things will happen:<br>
<br>
1) the mob is going to hit you for max damage because you were sitting<br>
2) the mob will attempt to hit you, either missing or causing regular damage.  However, this is because you stood up fast enought and taunt worked<br>
3) the mob will attempt to hit the other person because taunt failed.<br>
<br>
Regardless of which three things happen, sitting isn't adding any benifit.  It is however reducing your DPS and possibly increasing your damage taken.<br>
<br>
I think you're better off maintaining melee combat, which is interrupted when you sit, spam disarm and save taunt for when you loose agro. <p><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><center><tr><td valign="top" align="center"><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=11741" target="dorfsex"><img border="0" src="http://www.gaiahealing.com/everquest/turom_sig.jpg"></a><br><b><table style='filter: alpha(opacity=100, finishopacity=50, style=3, startx=85, finishx=20, starty=0, finishy=0')><font color=white face=verdana, arial, helvetica><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=11741" target="dorfsex"><font color=white><p align="center">Turom Toesmasher</font></a><font color=red> .o. </font><a href="http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior" target="dorfsex"><font color=white>61 Dwarven Warlord</font></a><br><a href="http://pub43.ezboard.com/b7thhammer" target="dorfsex"><font color="white">The Seventh Hammer</font></a></table></td></tr></b></center></table></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=brutultarewmarr>Brutul Tarew Marr</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Slayer of Whiners</span><br>  Posts: 962<br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/11/02 2:20:47 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2616.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.blackcompany.cc/member_pics/45.jpg height=185 width=100></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_sword.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Sit Agro</span><hr size=1> As the other said, sit aggro is gone as soon as you stand again, so sitting and then immediately standing back up wouldn't be too helpful.  The mob will turn and whack you once and then go back to what it was doing.<br>
<br>
Sit aggro can be very useful for positioning mobs on raids though, when something gets pushed into a wall or a corner where there is danger of it warping.  If you have good aggro, but can't move it just by backing up, you can just back up once, get summoned, then back up again to where you want it and sit.  If you had decent aggro when you started this, most likely the mob will run over to whack you and you will get aggro back as soon as you stand back up and start meleeing again.  Personally I do this all the time, but I don't think it would be productive to sit down during combat as a means of building aggro. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=6629">Brutul Vilesilencer</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://images.allposters.com/images/54/039_15016.jpg">Barbarian</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> Warlord of the <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.blackcompany.cc">Black Company</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.realpoor.com">Tarew Marr</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=baracasplaguebearer>Baracas Plaguebearer</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 10<br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/11/02 2:27:13 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2616.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_sword.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Sit Agro</span><hr size=1> Thanks guys, the help is apprieciatted <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://216.119.111.158/eddieland.gif"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=hobbitassassin>Hobbit Assassin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 15<br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/11/02 3:30:17 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2616.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_sword.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Sit Agro</span><hr size=1> I would like to see some other peoples thoughts on this, preferably after trying it first.<br>
<br>
despite the fact i dont have any parsing to justify using it (or have ever heard of other people even doing this), i will always sit-taunt-stand if i feel its important that i get a particular taunt off.<br>
<br>
The logic i used to explain why it could work is:<br>
<br>
Sitting doesnt add points to the hate list, instead it works as a multiplier to what you already have, like range from target and (possibly) level.<br>
<br>
Now, if your chance of a successful taunt is relative to your position on the hate list, or your final calculated hate number (as opposed to just unmodified hate points) then...<br>
<br>
a sitting warrior has a greater chance of achieving a successful taunt.<br>
<br>
When you stand up, as would be expected after a successful taunt, your now have the most raw hate points and hence maintain aggro.<br>
<br>
<br>
the problems Baracas raised are still valid.  if you cant safely take a full round of max attacks this shouldnt even be considered.  also it can scare the pants off or annoy others, particularly your cleric.<br>
<br>
i dont use this regularly, the lost amount aggro gained through those few missed attacks/procs makes it hard to justify attempting even your second sitting taunt, let alone third.  i find i just use it once or twice on bigger mobs where i can justify the negatives to improve my chances of pulling something off the shaman / wizzy / etc.<br>
<br>
~Jentii<br>
warlord<br>
gnome <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=khumak>Khumak</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Formidable Opponent</span><br>  Posts: 190<br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/11/02 4:17:40 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2616.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_sword.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Sit Agro</span><hr size=1> The main thing that I find sit aggro helpful for is moving a mob.  Many times I find that I have enough aggro to be the one taking all the hits but not enough aggro to move the mob.  If I back off a bit and sit I usually get summoned.  If I then back off again and sit the mob moves right to me.  If I did not get summoned when I sat the first time then the mob will not move. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=85547">Khumak</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
Overlord<br>
Mith Marr<br>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=farlanderb>FarlanderB</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 74<br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/11/02 5:07:08 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2616.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_sword.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Sit Agro</span><hr size=1> I move away and sit when I need the mob off a wall, or closer to a wall, a fireport, etc. Sit aggro is only present when your sitting, so standing up negates anything you aquired while you were down. I don't dare sit if I know that the wizard has been nuking too hard, or I've taking a lot of CH's, or it's unslowed, too much of a risk to loose it.<br>
<br>
And, umm, are we not supposed to be pressing taunt while we have aggro? That has always helped me. <p>[62 Warlord]<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong> Farlander</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> (Human)<!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END-->[33 Enchanter] <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong> Fainel</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> (High Elf)<!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--> [10 Paladin]<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong> Sabern</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> (Half Elf)<!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.guild-legerdemain.com">Legerdemain</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=errakk>Errakk</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/11/02 5:22:39 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2616.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_sword.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Sit Agro</span><hr size=1> Farlander,<br>
First of all, great to see another Human Warrior! Second, I believe the concensus is that hitting the Taunt button while you already have aggro is a waste - you do not add any hate by doin so, and then you have to wait till the timer re-pops the Taunt button before it is available again. Chances are, right after you mash the Taunt button, a caster will grab aggro from you, and you will not be able to re-taunt till after the button pops out.<br>
<br>
Errakk<br>
49 Human Warrior<br>
Prexus <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=farlanderb>FarlanderB</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 77<br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/11/02 5:28:40 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2616.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_sword.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Sit Agro</span><hr size=1> Humans rule. )<br>
<br>
